Java Collection  (Collections - Framework/API in the form of interfaces and classes)

1. The collection framework is nothing but the API which contains a number of interfaces and classes. The important interfaces in this API are:

A) Collection
B) List
C) Queue
D) Set

2. Why collection introduced? 
Ans: Arrays store multiple values but the size is fixed and it contains only one type of data ie.e. int. Arrays are not dynamically

3. Collections: 

A) Size is infinite
B) It can contain multiple type of data

4. Collection is an interface
The important classes of collection API are:
A) Maps - interface 
   a) HashMap - class
   b) HashTable - class
   c) TreeMap - class
   d) LinkedHashMap
B) Sets - interface 
   a) HashSet - class
   b) LinkedHashSet - class
   c) TreeSet - class
C) Lists - interface 
   a) ArrayList - class
   b) Vector - class
   c) LinkedList - class
D) Queue - interface 
   a) PriorityQueue - class
E) Utilities
   a) Collections - class
   b) Arrays - class